- Attrition probability is calculated using a Naive Bayes classifier;
- Customer satisfaction scores are compared against the average for their specific industry and employment status.

- High-risk customers are those with an attrition probability greater than 0.5;
- The average utilization ratio indicates how much of their credit limit customers are using on average;
- The risk rank is determined by the attrition probability within each education level.

